Colour Pattern. “Transparent shrimp lacking conspicuous pigment lines on carapace or abdomen (very faint lies may be present). Small but conspicuous black-and-white pigment body in end of last abdominal segment. Eggs dull green. Pleura of ovigerous female with thin white ventral border” (
Powell 1983
).

Distribution and habitat. Known from Senegal (
Holthuis 1980
), Liberia (
Rathbun 1900
;
Johnston 1906
;
Holthuis 1952
), Nigeria (
Balss 1916
), Gabon (
Thallwitz 1892
), Kabinda (
Lenz 1910
), Congo (
De Man 1923
, 1925 ;
Schmitt 1926
) and Southern Angola (
Balss 1916
). In fully marine and brackish water above about 10 ppt, especially along quiet muddy shores (
Powell 1983
).
